reviews.text: I ordered some pork dish from here before, and I actually got food poisoning, serious stomach aches for a day, vomited, next day saw the doctor (vomited again) and saw the doctor (New Town Doctor) and he confirmed I got food poisoning. No clue if their hygiene has improved since then, but I will not risk it. I am surprised people still eat them when I pass by. "Babe Cafe" next to them closed down, but they had rats running out of the kitchen into the mall.

It was quite good back to 2-3yrs ago.
Now I would go to Pho Le in town centre.

Wonder why a group of professional Japanese restaurant would choose raw marbled beef for Vietnamese Pho... 

Received a "pork chop" likely mixed by part of three different porkchop... Really interesting ... 

Taste is not bad but the quality of food really dropped a lot

Wait for a long long time to get 2 seats, but luckily all the food tastes fantastic. The pho is really big in size, it is 1.5x normal size. The rice roll is my favorite, mixing the fresh fruits and the shrimp rice roll together tastes unbelievably refreshing! But for the salad, far too little to justify the price...

Food was great and had good presentations. It's quite popular so you may need to wait during peak hours. Staff was friendly. Good place for group gathering or catch up with friends. The place had vegetarian menu. Price was slightly above average. If you are sharing dishes, it's about $150 - $200 per person but if you order things like noodles soup, it could be less than $100.

No clue why this place is still open. I ate some pork dish there before, and had stomach pain and vomiting a short while after. Saw a doctor the next day (vomited again before going) in tuen mun town centre and he said I had food poisoning and that he avoids restaurants because generally the hygiene sucks.
"Baby Cafe" (The Angela Baby endorsed place)next door to it closed down - they had mice and rats coming out of their kitchen. I doubt this place is much cleaner.

reviews.text: Vast selection of baby related merchandise, Parents favorite. A huge supermarket sits next to this department store as well. A true one stop shop for families
Huge mall, connected to other shopping as well.  Good transportation options in and out.
Great place for shopping, especially for beauty products! Family mall with everything you need.

Central location. Linked to 5 or 6 other shopping arcades. Linked to the subway line at Tuen Mun station. Many car parks, and some offer free parking with purchase. I'm happy with this place as I'm always able to find whatever I'm looking for here. Finding my car after getting parking ticket stamped is always a challenge tho.
This is the closest to home and what you get.ftom.anywhere, you get it here  mostly, why ho anywhere else. My kids are practical, when they are here, they love it just here.
